<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-6613 SERIES - REASSEMBLE -
        MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="18">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure the mainshaft in a vise equipped with brass jaws or wood blocks, pilot (front) end of
                the shaft up (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030j7">Figure 197</hotlnk>). Keep keyway in the mainshaft clear for insertion of the
                mainshaft key.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030j7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030j7" filename="../figg13/G13030J7.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 197. Secure Mainshaft in Vise</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the reverse gear washer at the reverse gear location. Align the slot of the
                tolerance washer with the keyway in the mainshaft and insert the key from the top to lock the washer in
                position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030j8">Figure 198</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030j8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030j8" filename="../figg13/G13030J8.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 198. Insert Key From Top to Lock Washer in Position</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the first and reverse sliding clutch, aligning the slot in the clutch with the key (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030j9">Figure 199</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030j9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030j9" filename="../figg13/G13030J9.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 199. Install First and Reverse Sliding Clutch</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the key and install the 1st speed gear splined washer. Align the keyway and lock in
                position with the key (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030k0">Figure 200</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030k0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030k0" filename="../figg13/G13030K0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 200. Install 1st Speed Gear Splined Washer and Align Keyway</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 1st speed gear on the splined washer with the clutching teeth facing down (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030k1">Figure 201</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030k1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030k1" filename="../figg13/G13030K1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 201. Install 1st Speed Gear on Splined Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 2nd speed gear against the 1st speed gear, clutching teeth up (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030k2">Figure 202</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030k2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030k2" filename="../figg13/G13030K2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 202. Install 2nd Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the key and insert the splined washer in the hub of the 2nd speed gear. Align the
                washer with the mainshaft splines and lock in position by installing the key (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030k3">Figure 203</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030k3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030k3" filename="../figg13/G13030K3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 203. Insert Splined Washer in Hub of 2nd Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert two screwdrivers between the 1st and 2nd speed gears 180 degrees from each other (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030k4">Figure 204</hotlnk>). Apply slight downward pressure on the screwdriver
                handles and insert a feeler gauge between the hubs of the gears. If there is too much clearance between
                the hubs of the gears, the tolerance washer in the 2nd speed gear should be replaced by a thicker
                washer. If there is not enough clearance between the hubs of the gears, the tolerance washer in the 2nd
                speed gear must be replaced with a thinner washer.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030k4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030k4" filename="../figg13/G13030K4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 204. Insert Screwdrivers Between 1st and 2nd Speed Gears</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 2nd and 3rd speed sliding clutch, aligning the slot in the clutch with the key (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030k5">Figure 205</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure>
                <graphic id="g13030k5" filename="../figg13/G13030K5.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Install 2nd and 3rd Speed Sliding Clutch</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Setting Correct Axial Clearances for Mainshaft Gears</emph>
            </para>
            <table id="t1303001">
                <title>Axial Clearance (End Play) Limits</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="2in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="2in" colsep="1"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Reverse Speed Gear</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Minimum of .005"</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Forward Speed Gears</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>.005" - .012"</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>Washers are used to obtain the correct limits; thicknesses are available as follows:</para>
            <table id="t1303002">
                <title>Washer Thickness and Colors</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="1.5in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="1.5in" colsep="1"/>
                    <thead valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Limits (Inch)</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Color Code</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>.259 - .261</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Orange</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>.264 - .266</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Purple</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>.269 - .271</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Yellow</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>.274 - .276</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Black</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>.279 - .281</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Red</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>Always use the low limit washer in the 1st gear and 3rd speed gear positions as shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030k6">Figure 206</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030k6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030k6" filename="../figg13/G13030K6.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 205. Always Use Low Limit Washer in 1st Gear and 3rd Speed Gear Positions</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 3rd gear splined washer on the mainshaft at 3rd speed gear location. It will be
                necessary to pull the key upward slightly to fit the splined washer in position on the shoulder of the
                mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030k7">Figure 207</hotlnk>). Re-position key so that the cross pin rests on top of
                the washer.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030k7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030k7" filename="../figg13/G13030K7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 206. Install 3rd Gear Splined Washer on Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 3rd speed gear on the splined washer, clutching teeth down (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030k8">Figure 208</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030k8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030k8" filename="../figg13/G13030K8.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 207. Install 3rd Speed Gear on Splined Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 4th speed gear against the 3rd speed gear, clutching teeth up (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030k9">Figure 209</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030k9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030k9" filename="../figg13/G13030K9.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 208. Install 4th Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 4th speed gear splined washer on the shaft and in the hub of the gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030l0">Figure 210</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030l0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030l0" filename="../figg13/G13030L0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 209. Install 4th Speed Gear Splined Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the snap ring in the groove in the mainshaft to secure the 4th speed gear splined
                washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030l1">Figure 211</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <para>Use the same procedure to check clearance between the 3rd and 4th speed gears as used to check 1st and
                2nd gear clearance. The clearance can be adjusted by installing different thickness tolerance washers in
                the 4th speed position.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030l1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030l1" filename="../figg13/G13030L1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 210. Install Snap Ring in Mainshaft Groove</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1"></para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Mark two adjacent teeth on the drive gear and the two teeth directly opposite for timing
                        purposes (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f13030l2">Figure 212</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f13030l2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030l2" filename="../figg13/G13030L2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 211. Mark Teeth For Timing Purposes</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 4th-5th speed sliding clutch on the shaft. One end of the clutch is marked
                "front." Make sure this end of the clutch is installed toward the front of the mainshaft. Install the
                drive gear against the 4th speed gear, clutching teeth toward the 4th speed gear and engaging the
                sliding clutch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030l3">Figure 213</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030l3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030l3" filename="../figg13/G13030L3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 212. Install 4th-5th Speed Sliding Clutch</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mainshaft from the vise. Place the reverse gear on the splined washer which is
                locked to the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030l4">Figure 214</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030l4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030l4" filename="../figg13/G13030L4.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 213. Place Reverse Gear on Splined Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
